The Ahmed Bola Tinubu team known as WAZOBIA has launched a campaign or­ganization in support of his ambition. The newly launches cam­paign organization known as the Senator Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu (SABAT 2023) was berth on Tuesday in Ibadan, the Capital City of Oyo State, with the intention to galvanize the patriotic cit­izens of Nigerian on the need to encourage and support Senator Bola Ahmed Tinubu. The Director General of the campaign organization, Mr. Patrick Olatunji brief­ing journalists about the development at the Ibadan Recreation Club maintained that SABAT is a subsidiaries of WASOBIA an association for community development with tentacles spreading across length and breadth of the country including the fed­eral capital territory. NYSC Gets Commendation On Innovative Service Delivery Absence of Governing Council Hindering AAU Progress, ASUU… Olatunji described Tinubu as a focused, brave, commit­ted and determined individ­ual that needed support of all Nigerians for he has over the years developed many leaders in different capacities. He urged the people of south west not to allow the personal interest to override the interest of majority, not­ed that the region lost the op­portunity of Chief Obafemi Awolowo and Chief MKO Abiola in the past, stressing that God has presented anoth­er opportunity for the region to rule the country again with the man every Nigerian is fa­miliar with. He said, “our country must be developed and to achieve that we need to embrace pa­triotism and shun tribalism and religious sentiment. The wind of globalization is now, we need an experienced and pragmatic leader like Tinubu to bail us out of this present and future effect of this on Nigeria. Also in his address, Na­tional Secretary of SABAT Gideon Balogun said, “We are going to shut down Ibadan come January 19th for the Tinubu solidarity rally.